x4freetext: 1 MV Tandetron accelerator (TDT)
A thin 9Be layer (65(10%) ug/cm2 thick) evaporated on
top of a self supporting Au foil (73(10%) ug/cm2
thick).
The nominal thickness was checked by proton-EBS
measurement at Ep=2 MeV which also confirmed that
C and O impurities were not greater than 5 ug/cm2.
Two double-sided Si strip detectors (1.5 mm
thick 16x16 segments, 50x50 mm2 area) placed 12 cm
from the target.
The solid angle was determined by measurement of
elastic scattering by additional irradiation with
an accuracy of 3%.
Approved by Georgios Provatas (2020-04-14)
